defaultGlaucoma “shared care” in the community has been trialled in a number of areas and shows that by monitoring glaucoma patients in the community instead of in a hospital setting it is possible to reduce capacity problems in eye hospitals. The College of Optometrists and The Royal College of Ophthalmologists have produced a review of these initiatives
