default8.5
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultLack of patient centred caredefault: Patients with diabetes struggle to balance their many health care appointments with work and family/childcare commitments and inevitably some appointments are missed. Health services should be designed around the patient so someone with diabetes can have their diabetic retinal screening, full eye examination and foot check all in one go - rather than three different appointments and visits to the hospital/optometry.
